main event: Two calls were received about a bright object in the sky near Ashford, Kent on September 20, 1956.
interesting points: The first call reported a bright object 10-15 miles SW of Ashford at 19.50 local time., The second call described a bright white disc approaching Manston at high speed., Reports were forwarded to the RAF which suggested they might have been seeing balloons., Information was received four days after the sighting., Witnesses' specific addresses were not documented, only their towns.
sighted object: a bright white disc in the sky
